html(lang="en")
    head
        include /src/base/head.pug
        title man azdavis
        style: include index.css
    body
        header.two
            div AZDAVIS(1)
            div AZDAVIS(1)
        section
            h2 NAME
            div azdavis - a guy with certain characteristics
        section
            h2 SYNOPSIS
            div #[b azdavis] [option]... [arg]...
        section
            h2 DESCRIPTION
            div
                p.
                    azdavis is a guy from the United States. He studies
                    computer science at Carnegie Mellon®. He created this
                    website and is a fan of symbols such as ™, ®, and ©.
                p.
                    azdavis spends most of his time browsing Hacker News™ and
                    other news websites. When he's not doing that, he may work
                    on his personal computer-science-y project du jour, read a
                    book, or fruitlessly attempt to learn #[span.ja 日本語] (known
                    to many as the Japanese language).
                p.
                    azdavis enjoys certain enjoyable activities, that among
                    these being tossing a Sportdisc™ (known to many as a
                    Frisbee®), playing Klaus Teuber's Catan® (known to many as
                    Settlers of Catan®), and copy-pasting from Stack Overflow™
                    (known to many as the act of programming).
        section
            h2 OPTIONS
            div
                h3 -h, --help
                .opt Display this help.
                h3 -v, --version
                .opt Display version information (current age in years).
                h3 -q, --quiet
                .opt Be quiet, only report errors. This is the default.
                h3 -v, --verbose
                .opt Be chatty. This can only be used in special cases.
                h3 -l &lt;code&gt;, --lang=&lt;code&gt;
                .opt.
                    Use the given language for communication, where
                    &lt;code&gt; is one of en or ja, for English or Japanese,
                    respectively. The default is en. Using ja may result in
                    poorly-constructed or grammatically incorrect sentences.
                    #[span.ja すみませんでした。]
        section
            h2 AUTHORS
            div Written by David and Karen Davis.
        section
            h2 SAYING HELLO
            div.
                Email
                #[a(href="mailto:?subject=Hello") ariel.z.X@icloud.com]
                (replace X with davis).
        section
            h2 COPYRIGHT
            div Copyright © #[span#now Now] Ariel Davis. All rights reserved.
        section
            h2 SEE ALSO
            div
                - const gh = "https://github.com/azdavis"
                p GitHub profile: #[a(href= gh)= gh]
                p A simple keyboard game: #[a(href= "/lgw")= "/lgw"]
                p A Catan® board generator: #[a(href= "/cbg")= "/cbg"]
        footer.two
            -
                const now = new Date()
                const tzOff = now.getTimezoneOffset() * 60000
                const nowWithOff = new Date(1 * now - tzOff).toISOString()
            div= nowWithOff.substring(0, 10)
            div AZDAVIS(1)
